</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 4:27
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='256432' id='t-256432'>CA: And a couple years after this,
you published this book:</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='259349' id='t-259349'>&quot;The Apartheid of Sex.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='261229' id='t-261229'>What was your thesis in this book?</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 4:34
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='263458' id='t-263458'>MR: My thesis in this book is that there
are seven billion people in the world,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='267800' id='t-267800'>and actually, seven billion unique ways
to express one's gender.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='273117' id='t-273117'>And while people may have
the genitals of a male or a female,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='279549' id='t-279549'>the genitals don't determine your gender</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='282591' id='t-282591'>or even really your sexual identity.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='285400' id='t-285400'>That's just a matter of anatomy</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='287095' id='t-287095'>and reproductive tracts,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='288906' id='t-288906'>and people could choose
